      <p>
        GhostSquad57 from the Egee.io community runs a Quake 2 server over at ghostsquad57.com:28501
      </p>
      <p>
        The recommended client for joining the server is <a href="https://www.yamagi.org/quake2/">Yamagi Quake 2</a>  which runs on Linux, Mac OS X, BSD (FreeBSD and OpenBSD) and Windows. 
        Any Quake 2 source port should connect to the server without any issues, but Yamagi Quake 2 is <b>strongly</b> recommended.
      </p>
      <p>
        • Hardware: the server uses an Intel i5-3550 at 3.3GHz and 16GBs of Ballistix Sport UDIMM Memory. For storage, the server uses a 250GB Samsung EVO SSD. The server is also equipped with an Intel Pro/1000 Dual Gigabit LAN NIC.<br>
